data.name: Lemon Herb Grilled Chicken with Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Roasted Brussels Sprouts
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy grilled chicken infused with fresh lemon and herbs, paired with creamy garlic mashed potatoes and crispy roasted Brussels sprouts for a delightful meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, combine lemon juice, olive oil, thyme, rosemary, salt, and pepper to create a marinade.
Add the chicken breasts to the marinade and let them sit for at least 30 minutes.
Preheat the grill to medium-high heat and cook the marinated chicken for 6-7 minutes on each side until fully cooked and juices run clear.
Meanwhile, peel and chop the potatoes, then boil them in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes.
Drain the potatoes and return them to the pot; add butter, minced garlic, and milk, then mash until creamy. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Trim the Brussels sprouts and cut them in half. Toss with olive oil, salt, and pepper, then roast in the oven at 400°F (200°C) for 20-25 minutes until golden and crispy.
Serve the grilled chicken alongside the garlic mashed potatoes and roasted Brussels sprouts.
